{"cursor":"3179","size":15,"audio":[],"cat":[],"tmpl":[],"currentlang":"en","linknr":102,"url":"Science_magazine","article":"\n\nA 'science magazine' is a periodical publication with news, opinions and reports\nabout science for a non-expert audience. A periodical publication for scientific\nexperts, in contrast, is called a \"scientific journal\". Science magazines are\nread by non-scientists and scientists who want accessible information on fields\noutside their specialization.\n\nArticles in science magazines are sometimes republished or summarized by the\ngeneral press.\n","recorded":1362124364,"portal":[],"list":[],"links":"103","instances":["magazine","magazine","magazine","italian_magazine","magazine","magazine","journal","magazine","magazine"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Science and technology magazines|","Lists of magazines","Science-related lists","Works about science| Magazines"],"headings":["Examples of general science magazines","See also"],"tags":[["science","journal"],["cosmos","magazine"],["focus","italian_magazine"],["http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=engineering_%26_industrial_review","eir---www.eironline.com&action=edit&redlink=1"],["bbc_knowledge","magazine"],["discover","magazine"],["popular_science","magazine"],["seed","magazine"],["astronomy","magazine"],["mercury","magazine"],["skeptic","u.s._magazine"],["seed","magazine"]],"image":["http://en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","http://bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"related":["Periodical_literature","Science","Expert","Scientific_journal","Magazine","Scientist","Academic_specialization","News","Scientific_American_Mind","Popular_science","Science_journalism"],"members":["skeptic","discover","astronomy","popular_science","focus","seed","mercury","science","bbc_knowledge","cosmos"],"book":[]}